description.narrative: By end 2022, key departments, public-sector institutions and stakeholders at national and provincial level have improved capacities to measure child poverty, increase public sector investments for children and design polices/programs and inclusive social protection systems by use of high-quality data, research and evaluative evidence., which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Cross Sectoral - Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change (Covid), Evaluation, Reducing Child Poverty, Research. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Effectively plan, monitor, evaluate and report on programme delivery.

description.narrative: UNICEF successfully completed social protection scoping mission, research study on impact of climate change, and MICS in Punjab, Sindh and KP.The efforts contributed significantly to upstream advocacy on child rights agenda through passage of three CRC-aligned legislations, increased allocation to social protection to address impact of COVID-19 on vulnerable populations, and more availability and use of equity-based evidence and data for policymakers and planners in domains concerning children and women. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/01/2022
